@node Introduction "What is MagicFile?!"
                                                                
@toc main
Introduction
------------
Everyone always likes the file-taggers we see on PC bbs's, so do I. When
I started coding my cdrom-door for Xenolink I played with some ideas and
really liked the idea of making a file-tagger for Xenolink, not only for
cdrom files,  but  also for the normal filecatalogue files.  The problem
was that I really couldn't do it in C,  I just started learning it. So I
waited  and I made my cdrom door piece by piece..  Very slowly it became
better and I became better at coding C.  So when Xenolink v1.90  arrived
and  after  a  while I released my cdrom door MagicCD I wanted to have a
try at  the filecatalogue version.  And it went really well actually,  I
had a working version in just one day!

So here it is, the first and @{b}ONLY@{ub} file-tagger for Xenolink!

                               @{b}MagicFile@{ub}

@endnode
@node features "Features of MagicFile"

Features
--------
These are some of MagicFile's features:

      - Supports Xenolinks filecatalogue.

      - Supports external configs for CDROM files.

      - Optional buffering of cdrom files to hard drive before download.

      - Supports and honours ALL access restrictions from template.config!

      - Supports external doors for eg. archive viewing, downloading,
        long descriptions etc. etc.

      - All text strings configurable.

      - All keys configurable.

      - Almost all colors configurable.

      - Online help through textfile.

      - NO fragmenting of hd (unlike some other cdrom doors)

      - Lots more, just see for yourself!

@endnode
@node MainConfig " "

Config files
------------

MagicFile has two different type of config files, they are:

 @{" <areaname>.cfg   " Link file}  -  Config with the filenames/descriptions
                          [CD mode only].

  <cdname>.config or 
 @{" MagicFile.config " Link <cdname>.config}  -  General configuration file
                         (only works for REGISTERED USERS!).


I have lots of 'ready-to-go' configs for all kinds of cd's on my bbs.
You can freq or just download them from my @{"bbs" link bbs}.

