@node <cdname>.config " "
                                                                            
@toc main
;
;
; MagicCD exampleconfig
;
; [Config will only be used by a registered MagicFile]
;

;
; String templates
;
WAITLOADING        "Please wait, loading..."
HEADER             "[44m  <[3mup[0;44m> Move Up - <[3mdown[0;44m> Move Down  - <[3mspc[0;44m> Tag a File - <?> Commands - <q> Quit[0m"
AREASTRING         "File-area:"

NOANSIMENUSET      "You need an ANSI menuset for MagicFile! <press key>"
NOVIEWACCESS       "You have no access to this file area! <press key>"
NOLISTACCESS       "You have no access to this file area! <press key>"

NODOWNLOADACCESS   "[0;32;3mYou have no Download access in this file area! <press key>[0m"
MAXMARKSEXCEEDED   "[0;32;3mYou may not mark any more files! <press key>[0m"
DAILYBYTESEXCEEDED "[0;32;3mFile exceeds daily download limit! <press key>[0m"
FILERATIOEXCEEDED  "[0;32;3mFile exceeds file ratio! <press key>[0m"
BYTERATIOEXCEEDED  "[0;32;3mFile exceeds byte ratio! <press key>[0m"

BEGINNINGOFLIST    "[0;32;3mBeginning of list! <press key>[0m"
ENDOFLIST          "[0;32;3mEnd of list! <press key>[0m"

BUFFERINGFILEWAIT  "[0;32;3mPlease wait, copying file to hd...[0m"
ERRORBUFFERINGFILE "[0;32;3m*** Error copying file, warn your sysop! *** <druk toets>[0m"

;
; Please NO ansi codes in the next 4 templates..
;
ENTERPATTERN       "Enter search pattern: "
SEARCHING          "Please wait, searching..."
FOUND              "Found!"
NOTFOUND           "Nothing matches pattern! <press key>"

;
; Color templates
;
COLORHEADER       "[44m"
COLORNAME         "[31m"
COLORSIZE         "[36m"
COLORDESC         "[37m"


;
; Other templates
;
;
; Maximum number of files that can be marked
;
MAXMARKS         5

;
; Helpscreen
;
HELPFILE         Doors:MagicFile/MagicFile.help

;
; If you want to buffer your CDROM files to hd before downloading,
; just remove the ';' and change the filepath to your prefs.
;
;BUFFERFILES      Xenolink:Temp/




;
; DOOR <stack> <argstring> <key> <key>
;
; <stack>           = Required stack for door
; <argstring>       = Argument string of door
; <key>             = Key to press to activate door
; <key>             = Second key, normally same key in uppercase
;
;
DOOR      4096  "Doors:MagicFile/Bin/Download           ~20"  "d"  "D"
DOOR      4096  "Doors:MagicFile/Bin/ViewArchive     ^F ~20"  "v"  "V"
DOOR      4096  "Doors:MagicFile/Bin/LongDescription ^F ~20"  "l"  "L"


;
; ACTION <action> <key> <key>
;
ACTION         HELP        "?"  "?"
ACTION         QUIT        "q"  "Q"
ACTION         SEARCH      "s"  "S"
ACTION         TAGFILE     " "  "0"
ACTION         FILEHOME    "7"  "7"
ACTION         FILEEND     "1"  "1"
ACTION         FILEUP      "8"  "8"
ACTION         FILEDOWN    "2"  "2"
ACTION         PAGEUP      "4"  "9"
ACTION         PAGEDOWN    "6"  "3"



@endnode
                                                                        
@node file " "
@toc main


Filedata configs
----------------

The filedata configs are in the following format:

<filename>                (max. 30 chars)
<filesize>                (max.  8 chars)
<description>             (max. 60 chars)
<complete path of file>   (max. 50 chars)

example:

TESTFILE10.LHA
101220
Testfile v1.0 - Testfile for the example.
CD0:TESTDIR/FILES/
TESTFILE11.LHA
101221
Testfile v1.1 - Testfile for the example.
CD0:TESTDIR/FILES/
TESTFILE12.LHA
101222
Testfile v1.2 - Testfile for the example.
CD0:TESTDIR/FILES/
TESTFILE13.LHA
101223
Testfile v1.3 - Testfile for the example.
CD0:TESTDIR/FILES/


@endnode
@node installation "Installing MagicFile"
@toc main

Installation
------------

Just copy the whole MagicFile directory to 'DOORS:' and put it in your
whatevermenu.src.

MagicFile uses ReadArgs() for it's command line parsing.

Here are the keywords:

MODE/K/A           Mode to start the door in,  CD for the cd mode,  and XLK
                   for the filecatalogue mode, required!

CONFIG/K           The general config file to load, if this keyword is left
                   out,  MagicFile will take MagicFile.config  as a general
                   config. This way you won't have to make a general config
                   file for each area you've got.  Then  again you CAN make
                   every area listing look different if you want to.  Strip
                   'Doors:MagicFile/' from the path.

AREA/K             Filearea to load, usually ~561, or just the number..

DATA/K             Filedata config.
                   Again: strip 'Doors:MagicFile/' from the path!

XCBD/K/A           Should always be ~20, required!


EXAMPLES
--------

For your cdrom area's something like this:

CMD = "1"
{
XenolinkDoor "^10000^3^Doors:MagicFile/MagicFile MODE=CD DATA=100200.cfg XCBD=~20"
}

CMD = "2"
{
XenolinkDoor "^10000^3^Doors:MagicFile/MagicFile MODE=CD CONFIG=test.config DATA=200300.cfg XCBD=~20"
}

And for your normal file area's something like this:

CMD = "3"
{
XenolinkDoor "^10000^3^Doors:MagicFile/MagicFile MODE=XLK AREA=3 XCBD=~20"
}

CMD = "4"
{
ChangeFileArea "4"
XenolinkDoor "^10000^3^Doors:MagicFile/MagicFile MODE=XLK AREA=~561 XCBD=~20"
}

(~561 is the current file area)

@endnode
@node How_To " "
@toc main

How to register
---------------

MagicFile is a shareware program, this  means  you can try it out for free
but if you like it you must pay a shareware fee to the author (that's me).

When you register you'll get

 - BroodVerdeler, this utility can convert about 90% of the existing
    cdrom filelistings into a MagicFile config. <when it's ready>

 - An external search door. <when it's ready>

 - A keyfile which will enable you to use the MagicFile.config

 - And the keyfile will also make my future 'Magic' doors registered.


I have set the fee as following:

Dutch guys, CASH IN ENVELOPE   35,-    (35 Dutch guilders)

Other, CASH IN ENVELOPE        US$25,- (25 American dollars)

Other, BY EUROCHEQUE           45,-    (45 Dutch guilders, no other currenties!)


There is one more option, if you have some nice Magic, The Gathering
cards i might want to trade them for a keyfile. Contact me through the
Xenolink echo's, netmail or my @{"bbs" Link BBS}.

Fill in the registration.form you found in the archive and send it together
with the money to my address  (which you can find at the bottom of
registration.form).

When I have received the money I'll crash the key to your fidonet number,
if you don't have one you can download the key at my @{"bbs" Link BBS}.
@endnode
