@node Changes " "

[WARNING: Changes have been made to the main-config file, please
 check the supplied examples for the correct changes!]

 - Fixed bug in CD mode where filedescriptions above 45 chars would
   be cut off.


 - Added optional 'buffering' of files.  Files (from cdrom) can be buffered
   to harddisk for speed and or multinode bbs's with cd-changers.
   keyword:

   BUFFERFILES <path>

   If you don't want your cdrom files to be buffered, just comment
   it out with a ';'


 - Added 'ACTION' template in config.  Works as follows:

   ACTION <action> <key> <key>

   Actions:

            HELP        Help screen
            QUIT        Quit door
            SEARCH      Search on filenaam/description
            TAGFILE     Tag/mark a file for downloading
            FILEHOME    Goto beginning of filelist
            FILEEND     Goto end of filelist
            FILEUP      One file up
            FILEDOWN    One file down
            PAGEUP      One 'page' up
            PAGEDOWN    One 'page' down

   <key> and <key> are the key's to press to activate the 'action'
   (usually lower and uppercase of the same letter)


 - Added 'DOOR' template in config.  Works as follows:

   DOOR <stack> <argstring> <key> <key>

   <stack>           = Required stack for door
   <argstring>       = Argument string of door
   <key>             = Key to press to activate door
   <key>             = second key, normally same key in lowercase

   Cookies for argstring:
   ~20 - XCB pointer

   ^F  - Path+Name of file currently under tagger (for archive handler or
         long descriptions/file-info viewer)

   All user and xcb-related ~ codes work too..


 - Added numerous string templates in the config, check example config
   for templates.


 - Put helpscreen in an external file, keyword for config:

    HELPFILE <filename>


 - Improved the marking of cdrom files, now files AND bytes will be
   added to the users stats (Only if file WAS actually downloaded)


 - Added checking for menuset.  Now MagicFile only starts with a menuset
   1 or higher, if a user with menuset 0 enters MagicFile, a message will
   come up saying he should change to an ANSI menuset.


 - Added little archive viewer, removed the arexx script.


 - Added long description viewer, removed the arexx script.


 - Added file/byte ratio checker.


 - Added maxbytesperday checker.


 - Added filearea view/list/download access checker


@endnode
                                                                                                                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                
          